This directory structure contains the functional and unittests

If you wish to contribute to this project, please make your own tests too and
be shoure, that all tests are running correctly after extending the sources.

The tests depend on phpunit 3.4.6. It is the best if you install it 
following by the intructions from here:
http://www.phpunit.de/manual/current/en/installation.html

The directory structure:

functional
	This files tests wether the showcase runs correctly in a browser or not.
	
	The tests are here depends on the selenium here you can find a start
	documentation about it:
	http://seleniumhq.org/projects/remote-control/
	You can dowload it here:
	http://seleniumhq.org/download/
	You can start it that easy:
	http://seleniumhq.org/docs/05_selenium_rc.html#installation
	You have to arrange a in the setup.php file the basepath url of the 
	showcase directory deployed. If you have firefox installed, after all just 
	type in	"phpunit functional" from this directory if you wish to test the 
	functionailty of the framework.
	
unit
	The unittests belogs to this directory just type in from this directory: 
	"phpunit unit" and the results should come. 
	